Explanation:
We iterate through the characters of the string s twice, comparing each character with the first two characters of the target string. If a match is found, we increment the count and break the inner loop. This solution has a time complexity of O(n^2) because of the nested loops, where n is the length of the string s. The space complexity is O(1) since we only use a single integer variable for counting the matches. The energy implications are low because the solution only involves simple comparisons and does not require any complex operations.

